Cook and drain ravioli as directed on package. In 10-inch skillet, heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook 2 to 4 minutes, turning occasionally, until brown. Stir in cooking sauce, cooked ravioli and half-and-half; reduce heat. Simmer uncovered 3 to 5 minutes or until sauce is hot. Sprinkle with bacon, cheese and basil.